cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.NE, cs.EM, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses the use of resistive devices for deep learning hardware designs, which can be considered an emerging technology. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper focuses on the design of a hardware architecture for in-memory computing using RRAM and CMOS technology. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper specifically targets binary deep neural networks and discusses the accuracy and efficiency of the proposed design. 
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems): The proposed design is intended for use in area-/energy-constrained edge computing devices, which can be considered embedded systems. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper evaluates the proposed design using two popular image datasets, MNIST and CIFAR-10, which are commonly used in computer vision research.
